# Configuration

## Environment variables

Copy the example file and edit:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `LLM_PROVIDER` | Yes | `ollama` | `ollama` or `gemini` |
| `DEFAULT_MODEL` | Yes | `gemma3:4b` | Model name passed to the provider |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | When using Gemini | — | Your Google Gemini API key |
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | No | — | GitHub personal access token for higher API rate limits |

## Provider mapping

Provider routing lives in `prompt.py` and `models.py`:

- **Ollama** — `models.OllamaProvider` wraps `ollama.chat` directly
- **Gemini** — `models.GeminiProvider` adapts Gemini responses to a unified format

## Development mode

`config.py` has a single toggle:

```python
DEVELOPMENT_MODE = True   # enables caching + CSV export
```

When on:

- Intermediate results are cached to `cache/` (speeds up iteration)
- Each run appends a row to `resume_evaluations.csv`
- Useful for batch processing and debugging

## File layout

```
amphib/
├── config.py           # development mode flag
├── .env                # your local environment variables
├── .env.example        # template for .env
├── cache/              # cached intermediate results (gitignored)
└── resume_evaluations.csv  # scored results (gitignored)
```

